                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1110" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1110" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1110" type="surname" value="GRIFFITH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1110" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS GRIFFITH</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the service of Thomas M'Car thy, and live in Jubilee-place, Chelsea. He bought some green-houses, and I was employed to pull them down—I missed a frame and glass—I found a policeman, and went with him to the prisoner's house, in Simmonds-street—I found the prisoner on the works, in the same ground where the frame was taken from—I found the frame at the head of the prisoner's bed—he went there with us.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross rexamined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Have you any doubt it was the sash? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> None—he said if I would forgive him he would give up the sash—I then went to his house and got it.</p>
